DOM(Document obect model)
	It is programming interface in wed development that allows us to interact and manipulate (change) the html documents
	When the web page is loaded , the browser create the Dom of the webpage
	when the html file is loaded in the browser , the javascript cannot understand the  html document directly
DOM: is basically the representation of same html document but in a tree-like structure composed of objects
Html DOM allow javascript to access (to get ) and modify all the elements in the document
Key points:
1)structure:the dom represents the structure of html document as tree ; each node in a tree represent the element,an attribute,text
2)manipulation: using js,you can interact with elements(buttons , h, p), we can modify , add , remove elements change style;
3)event handling:
4)w3c-world wide web consortium
-- in dom all html elements are defind  objects.
Property: is a value that you can set to the object
(like changing content of an html element)
Method: an action 
(like add or delete)
Methods of document object:
Getting element
1)getting an element by id
2)getting an element by class:
---returns all the elements havig the same class name
---returns the form of html collection object
3)getting an element by tagname
4)getting an element by query selector methods :
 * query selector
 * query selector all
